# Backend Code Patterns

## Module Structure
Every feature module in `src/modules/{name}/` must have exactly:
- `{name}.routes.ts` — Express Router only; no business logic
- `{name}.service.ts` — business logic; calls adapters/repos
- `{name}.repository.ts` — Prisma queries only
- `{name}.schema.ts` — Zod validation schemas
- `{name}.types.ts` — module-local TS types (if needed)

## Route Handler Pattern
```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT — route calls service, no logic in handler
router.post('/resource', validate({ body: schema }), asyncHandler(async (req, res) => {
  const result = await service.doThing(req.auth, req.tenantPrisma, req.body);
  res.status(201).json({ data: result, meta: { requestId: uuidv4(), timestamp: new Date().toISOString() } });
}));

// ❌ WRONG — business logic in route handler
router.post('/resource', asyncHandler(async (req, res) => {
  const patient = await prisma.patient.findUnique({ where: { id: req.body.patientId } });
  // ... more logic
}));
```

## Adapter Usage
```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT — import from index (factory), not concrete adapter
import { getAiChatAdapter } from '../../adapters/ai/index.js';

// ❌ WRONG — import concrete adapter directly
import { createOpenRouterAdapter } from '../../adapters/ai/openrouter.adapter.js';
```

## PHI Access Pattern
```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT — always audit PHI access
await auditLog({ tenantPrisma, userId: auth.userId, orgId: auth.orgId,
  action: 'READ_RECORD', resourceType: 'Patient', resourceId: patientId });

// ❌ WRONG — reading PHI without audit log
const patient = await tenantPrisma.patient.findUnique({ where: { id } });
return patient;
```

## Error Handling
```typescript
// ✅ Use typed errors from src/core/errors.ts
throw new NotFoundError('Patient not found');
throw new ForbiddenError('Access denied');
throw new ValidationError('Invalid input', zodIssues);

// ❌ Never throw raw errors in service layer
throw new Error('something went wrong');
```

## File Extensions
All imports in `.ts` files must use `.js` extension (NodeNext module resolution):
```typescript
import { foo } from './foo.js'; // ✅
import { foo } from './foo';    // ❌
```
